question: Which self-improvement actions maximize quality-per-overhead under live workload?
method: Cross-session action-type audit (S306-S331): enumerate action types, extract avg L/P/K_delta yields from session logs, score by quality composite

ranking.notes: Highest L/P yield. One artifact per session. 100% MERGED.
Unique structural value: K_avg growth. Low L/P but irreplaceable for graph density.

ranking.evidence: L-374, L-407, L-458 from S306-S330 signals. Multiple per-signal artifacts.
ranking.notes: Signal quality varies (high-specificity: 67% canonical, bare: 36%). Depends on human.

ranking.evidence: S306 tool-audit, S329 periodics-meta-audit, S325 bridge-sync, S331 tool-audit
ranking.notes: Preventive maintenance. 0-1 L per audit. Catches silent drift before it compounds.

ranking.evidence: S330 65 lessons trimmed; S331 21 lessons trimmed
ranking.notes: Pure maintenance. 0 L/P. Prevents check.sh DUE accumulation.

ranking.notes: 0 L/P. Improves ISO density metric. Zero ROI when dark_matter already 0%.

ranking.notes: Pure bookkeeping. Required every session. Irreducible overhead.

findings: DOMEX expert sessions are highest-yield action type (L=1.5/session, artifact_rate=1.0, 100% MERGED)
Citation sprints unique: 0 L/P but irreplaceable K_avg growth (+0.37/session). Can't be substituted.
Maintenance actions (trim, sync, ISO) collectively 0 L/P but prevent DUE accumulation — necessary but not sufficient
ISO annotation has zero ROI when dark_matter=0%; cadence should auto-suppress
State-sync is irreducible overhead (required every session); optimize for speed, not elimination
Human-signal response is medium-yield but signal-quality dependent; high-specificity signals 67% canonical vs 36% for bare signals
prescription: Maximize: DOMEX expert sessions (F-EXP7 protocol, one-shot, target ≥15% utilization)
Sustain: citation sprints every 20-30 sessions to prevent K_avg decay
Batch: maintenance (trim, sync) once per session at end, not spread across session
Suppress: ISO annotation when dark_matter=0%; periodic audits only when DUE
verdict: BASELINE ESTABLISHED (n=25 sessions, 7 action types). DOMEX > citation_sprint > human-signal > periodic_audit > maintenance. Maintenance is necessary but not value-generating. Session quality = maximize DOMEX ratio.
